{
  "doc_id": "56420",
  "text": "It is clearly argued in [CITATION_1] that F O[Succ]-definable tree languages are exactly the locally threshold testable languages, for general model-theoretic reasons, but that this fact alone does not directly yield a decision procedure. The result stated above is analogous to the characterization of F O[Succ]-definability for recognizable word languages -more precisely, Condition (1) suffices for languages of words and their syntactic semigroups. Condition (2) , which makes sense in trees but not in words, must be added to the other one to characterize F O[Succ]-definability for tree languages.",
